"{\"uid\": \"fansided.com-posts-olympic-beach-volleyball-rules-explaining-paris-2024\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"TheParis 2024 Olympicsare in full swing, and it's a glorious sight to behold for sports fans.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 93, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"TheParis 2024 Olympicsare\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 25}, {\"ngram\": \"full swing\", \"from\": 29, \"to\": 39}, {\"ngram\": \"a glorious sight\", \"from\": 50, \"to\": 66}, {\"ngram\": \"sports fans\", \"from\": 81, \"to\": 92}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At any given moment of the day, there are dozens of different events happening in the City of Light, from table tennis to archery and badminton to gymnastics.\", \"from\": 94, \"to\": 252, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"any given moment\", \"from\": 97, \"to\": 113}, {\"ngram\": \"the day\", \"from\": 117, \"to\": 124}, {\"ngram\": \"dozens\", \"from\": 136, \"to\": 142}, {\"ngram\": \"different events\", \"from\": 146, \"to\": 162}, {\"ngram\": \"the City\", \"from\": 176, \"to\": 184}, {\"ngram\": \"Light\", \"from\": 188, \"to\": 193}, {\"ngram\": \"table tennis\", \"from\": 200, \"to\": 212}, {\"ngram\": \"archery\", \"from\": 216, \"to\": 223}, {\"ngram\": \"badminton\", \"from\": 228, \"to\": 237}, {\"ngram\": \"gymnastics\", \"from\": 241, \"to\": 251}]}, {\"sentence\": \"One of the most entertaining sports to watch in these Olympics, and certainly one of the most scenic, due to its being contested with the Eiffel Tower as a backdrop, is beach volleyball.\", \"from\": 254, \"to\": 440, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the most entertaining sports\", \"from\": 261, \"to\": 289}, {\"ngram\": \"these Olympics\", \"from\": 302, \"to\": 316}, {\"ngram\": \"the Eiffel Tower\", \"from\": 388, \"to\": 404}, {\"ngram\": \"a backdrop\", \"from\": 408, \"to\": 418}, {\"ngram\": \"beach volleyball\", \"from\": 423, \"to\": 439}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Most sports fans know the general rules of soccer, basketball, or the 100-meter dash, but when it comes to sports that the casual fan does not often watch outside the Olympics, it can be an uphill battle to understand exactly what is going on.\", \"from\": 441, \"to\": 684, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Most sports fans\", \"from\": 441, \"to\": 457}, {\"ngram\": \"the general rules\", \"from\": 463, \"to\": 480}, {\"ngram\": \"soccer\", \"from\": 484, \"to\": 490}, {\"ngram\": \"basketball\", \"from\": 492, \"to\": 502}, {\"ngram\": \"the 100-meter dash\", \"from\": 507, \"to\": 525}, {\"ngram\": \"sports\", \"from\": 548, \"to\": 554}, {\"ngram\": \"the casual fan\", \"from\": 560, \"to\": 574}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 604, \"to\": 616}, {\"ngram\": \"an uphill battle\", \"from\": 628, \"to\": 644}, {\"ngram\": \"exactly what\", \"from\": 659, \"to\": 671}]}, {\"sentence\": \"FanSided is here to get you up to speed on all of the bumping, setting, and spiking, so by the time the medal rounds begin, you will be a newly minted expert on a sport that the United States has long excelled at.\", \"from\": 686, \"to\": 899, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 686, \"end\": 694, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FanSided\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"FanSided\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FanSided\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/FanSided\"}, {\"begin\": 864, \"end\": 877, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9998467796950898, \"rank\": 0.0001532195112640834, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"speed\", \"from\": 720, \"to\": 725}, {\"ngram\": \"the bumping\", \"from\": 736, \"to\": 747}, {\"ngram\": \"the time\", \"from\": 777, \"to\": 785}, {\"ngram\": \"the medal\", \"from\": 786, \"to\": 795}, {\"ngram\": \"a newly minted expert\", \"from\": 822, \"to\": 843}, {\"ngram\": \"a sport\", \"from\": 847, \"to\": 854}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Beach volleyball differs from its indoor counterpart in that each match is a 2v2 affair, but the rules of play are the same.\", \"from\": 901, \"to\": 1025, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Beach volleyball\", \"from\": 901, \"to\": 917}, {\"ngram\": \"its indoor counterpart\", \"from\": 931, \"to\": 953}, {\"ngram\": \"each match\", \"from\": 962, \"to\": 972}, {\"ngram\": \"a 2v2 affair\", \"from\": 976, \"to\": 988}, {\"ngram\": \"the rules\", \"from\": 994, \"to\": 1003}, {\"ngram\": \"play\", \"from\": 1007, \"to\": 1011}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Each point begins with a serve that must clear the net in one hit.\", \"from\": 1026, \"to\": 1092, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Each point\", \"from\": 1026, \"to\": 1036}, {\"ngram\": \"a serve\", \"from\": 1049, \"to\": 1056}, {\"ngram\": \"the net\", \"from\": 1073, \"to\": 1080}, {\"ngram\": \"one hit\", \"from\": 1084, \"to\": 1091}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After that, each team is allowed to touch the ball three times before it must go back over the net, but teammates must alternate shots.\", \"from\": 1093, \"to\": 1228, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"each team\", \"from\": 1105, \"to\": 1114}, {\"ngram\": \"the ball\", \"from\": 1135, \"to\": 1143}, {\"ngram\": \"the net\", \"from\": 1184, \"to\": 1191}, {\"ngram\": \"teammates\", \"from\": 1197, \"to\": 1206}, {\"ngram\": \"shots\", \"from\": 1222, \"to\": 1227}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A player can not hit the ball twice in a row, with one exception: if they block a ball at the net, they can then hit the next shot as well.\", \"from\": 1229, \"to\": 1368, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A player\", \"from\": 1229, \"to\": 1237}, {\"ngram\": \"the ball\", \"from\": 1250, \"to\": 1258}, {\"ngram\": \"a row\", \"from\": 1268, \"to\": 1273}, {\"ngram\": \"one exception\", \"from\": 1280, \"to\": 1293}, {\"ngram\": \"a ball\", \"from\": 1309, \"to\": 1315}, {\"ngram\": \"the net\", \"from\": 1319, \"to\": 1326}, {\"ngram\": \"the next shot\", \"from\": 1346, \"to\": 1359}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A point ends when the ball touches the ground (either in- or out-of-bounds), a team hits the ball more than three times, or a player touches the ball twice in a row illegally.\", \"from\": 1369, \"to\": 1544, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A point\", \"from\": 1369, \"to\": 1376}, {\"ngram\": \"the ball\", \"from\": 1387, \"to\": 1395}, {\"ngram\": \"the ground\", \"from\": 1404, \"to\": 1414}, {\"ngram\": \"bounds\", \"from\": 1437, \"to\": 1443}, {\"ngram\": \"a team\", \"from\": 1446, \"to\": 1452}, {\"ngram\": \"the ball\", \"from\": 1458, \"to\": 1466}, {\"ngram\": \"a player\", \"from\": 1493, \"to\": 1501}, {\"ngram\": \"the ball\", \"from\": 1510, \"to\": 1518}, {\"ngram\": \"a row\", \"from\": 1528, \"to\": 1533}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A point will also end if a player touches the net, which can sometimes happen when attempting to block a shot.\", \"from\": 1545, \"to\": 1655, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A point\", \"from\": 1545, \"to\": 1552}, {\"ngram\": \"a player\", \"from\": 1570, \"to\": 1578}, {\"ngram\": \"the net\", \"from\": 1587, \"to\": 1594}, {\"ngram\": \"a shot\", \"from\": 1648, \"to\": 1654}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Beach volleyball features rally scoring, which means that when a team wins a point, their score goes up by one.\", \"from\": 1657, \"to\": 1768, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Beach volleyball\", \"from\": 1657, \"to\": 1673}, {\"ngram\": \"rally scoring\", \"from\": 1683, \"to\": 1696}, {\"ngram\": \"a team\", \"from\": 1720, \"to\": 1726}, {\"ngram\": \"a point\", \"from\": 1732, \"to\": 1739}, {\"ngram\": \"their score\", \"from\": 1741, \"to\": 1752}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This differs from traditional scoring, as points used to be awarded only to the serving team.\", \"from\": 1769, \"to\": 1862, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"traditional scoring\", \"from\": 1787, \"to\": 1806}, {\"ngram\": \"points\", \"from\": 1811, \"to\": 1817}, {\"ngram\": \"the serving team\", \"from\": 1845, \"to\": 1861}]}, {\"sentence\": \"With rally scoring, the team that wins the point also wins the right to serve the next point.\", \"from\": 1863, \"to\": 1956, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"rally scoring\", \"from\": 1868, \"to\": 1881}, {\"ngram\": \"the team\", \"from\": 1883, \"to\": 1891}, {\"ngram\": \"the point\", \"from\": 1902, \"to\": 1911}, {\"ngram\": \"the right\", \"from\": 1922, \"to\": 1931}, {\"ngram\": \"the next point\", \"from\": 1941, \"to\": 1955}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Each Olympic beach volleyball match consists of a best two-out-of-three set format.\", \"from\": 1958, \"to\": 2041, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Each Olympic beach volleyball match\", \"from\": 1958, \"to\": 1993}, {\"ngram\": \"a best two-out-of-three set format\", \"from\": 2006, \"to\": 2040}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The first two sets are played as a race to 21, with each team needing to win by two to secure the set.\", \"from\": 2042, \"to\": 2144, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The first two sets\", \"from\": 2042, \"to\": 2060}, {\"ngram\": \"a race\", \"from\": 2075, \"to\": 2081}, {\"ngram\": \"each team\", \"from\": 2094, \"to\": 2103}, {\"ngram\": \"the set\", \"from\": 2136, \"to\": 2143}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the case of a tie after the first two sets, the third set is played as a race to 15.\", \"from\": 2145, \"to\": 2232, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the case\", \"from\": 2148, \"to\": 2156}, {\"ngram\": \"a tie\", \"from\": 2160, \"to\": 2165}, {\"ngram\": \"the first two sets\", \"from\": 2172, \"to\": 2190}, {\"ngram\": \"the third set\", \"from\": 2192, \"to\": 2205}, {\"ngram\": \"a race\", \"from\": 2219, \"to\": 2225}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There are two divisions in Olympic beach volleyball: men's and women's.\", \"from\": 2234, \"to\": 2305, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"two divisions\", \"from\": 2244, \"to\": 2257}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympic beach volleyball\", \"from\": 2261, \"to\": 2285}, {\"ngram\": \"men\", \"from\": 2287, \"to\": 2290}, {\"ngram\": \"women\", \"from\": 2297, \"to\": 2302}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There are 24 teams in each division, with teams divided into six groups of four each.\", \"from\": 2306, \"to\": 2391, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"24 teams\", \"from\": 2316, \"to\": 2324}, {\"ngram\": \"each division\", \"from\": 2328, \"to\": 2341}, {\"ngram\": \"teams\", \"from\": 2348, \"to\": 2353}, {\"ngram\": \"six groups\", \"from\": 2367, \"to\": 2377}, {\"ngram\": \"four each\", \"from\": 2381, \"to\": 2390}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Each team plays the other three teams in its group in a round robin format, with the top two teams from each group and the top two third-place teams advancing to the elimination round.\", \"from\": 2392, \"to\": 2576, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Each team\", \"from\": 2392, \"to\": 2401}, {\"ngram\": \"the other three teams\", \"from\": 2408, \"to\": 2429}, {\"ngram\": \"its group\", \"from\": 2433, \"to\": 2442}, {\"ngram\": \"a round robin format\", \"from\": 2446, \"to\": 2466}, {\"ngram\": \"the top two teams\", \"from\": 2473, \"to\": 2490}, {\"ngram\": \"each group\", \"from\": 2496, \"to\": 2506}, {\"ngram\": \"the top two third-place teams\", \"from\": 2511, \"to\": 2540}, {\"ngram\": \"the elimination round\", \"from\": 2554, \"to\": 2575}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The other four third-place team will then face off, with the two winners also joining the elimination round.\", \"from\": 2577, \"to\": 2685, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The other four third-place team\", \"from\": 2577, \"to\": 2608}, {\"ngram\": \"the two winners\", \"from\": 2634, \"to\": 2649}, {\"ngram\": \"the elimination round\", \"from\": 2663, \"to\": 2684}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This pares the field down to 16 teams in each division, and from that point forward, a loss means elimination from the tournament.\", \"from\": 2687, \"to\": 2817, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the field\", \"from\": 2698, \"to\": 2707}, {\"ngram\": \"16 teams\", \"from\": 2716, \"to\": 2724}, {\"ngram\": \"each division\", \"from\": 2728, \"to\": 2741}, {\"ngram\": \"that point\", \"from\": 2752, \"to\": 2762}, {\"ngram\": \"a loss\", \"from\": 2772, \"to\": 2778}, {\"ngram\": \"elimination\", \"from\": 2785, \"to\": 2796}, {\"ngram\": \"the tournament\", \"from\": 2802, \"to\": 2816}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Teams that make it to the final four will then play for the medals, with the semifinal winners meeting to determine gold and silver, and the semifinals losers meeting to play for bronze.\", \"from\": 2818, \"to\": 3004, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Teams\", \"from\": 2818, \"to\": 2823}, {\"ngram\": \"the medals\", \"from\": 2874, \"to\": 2884}, {\"ngram\": \"the semifinal winners\", \"from\": 2891, \"to\": 2912}, {\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 2934, \"to\": 2938}, {\"ngram\": \"silver\", \"from\": 2943, \"to\": 2949}, {\"ngram\": \"the semifinals losers\", \"from\": 2955, \"to\": 2976}, {\"ngram\": \"bronze\", \"from\": 2997, \"to\": 3003}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Just as they would in a tennis tiebreaker, teams change sides every seven points during the first two sets.\", \"from\": 3006, \"to\": 3113, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a tennis tiebreaker\", \"from\": 3028, \"to\": 3047}, {\"ngram\": \"teams\", \"from\": 3049, \"to\": 3054}, {\"ngram\": \"sides\", \"from\": 3062, \"to\": 3067}, {\"ngram\": \"the first two sets\", \"from\": 3094, \"to\": 3112}]}, {\"sentence\": \"If the match reaches a third set, teams change sides every five points.\", \"from\": 3114, \"to\": 3185, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the match\", \"from\": 3117, \"to\": 3126}, {\"ngram\": \"a third set\", \"from\": 3135, \"to\": 3146}, {\"ngram\": \"teams\", \"from\": 3148, \"to\": 3153}, {\"ngram\": \"sides\", \"from\": 3161, \"to\": 3166}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Each team is allowed one timeout in each set, with an additional \\\"Technical Timeout\\\" being called automatically when the teams reach a combined score of 21 in each of the first two sets.\", \"from\": 3186, \"to\": 3372, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Each team\", \"from\": 3186, \"to\": 3195}, {\"ngram\": \"one timeout\", \"from\": 3207, \"to\": 3218}, {\"ngram\": \"each set\", \"from\": 3222, \"to\": 3230}, {\"ngram\": \"an additional \\\"Technical Timeout\", \"from\": 3237, \"to\": 3269}, {\"ngram\": \"the teams\", \"from\": 3303, \"to\": 3312}, {\"ngram\": \"a combined score\", \"from\": 3319, \"to\": 3335}, {\"ngram\": \"the first two sets\", \"from\": 3353, \"to\": 3371}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The defending Olympic champions in beach volleyball are Norway in the men's division and the United States in the women's division.\", \"from\": 3374, \"to\": 3505, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3430, \"end\": 3436, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Norway_women's_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999495586824244, \"rank\": 4.320724471438375e-05, \"text\": \"Norway\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Norway_women's_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Norway_women's_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 3467, \"end\": 3480, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9998467796950898, \"rank\": 0.0001532195112640834, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/r